content: Challenging puzzles, still trying to understand all the connections, but enjoying it!

I love this game, I feel like a detective, following the clues and deciphering everything. It's beautifully designed, I just wish some of the puzzles were a little more difficult, but there are a few really hard one in the mix, so I'm no complaining too much! I love the diversity of the puzzles as well.
It's fairly intriguing in its presentation and mechanic but what's the use when you go back and forth between levels as you please, with no indicator whether you've already solved one?
Its ok. Feel lost sometimes and feel the difficulty rises and falls like hills. I feel it should curve like a log.

I tried The Guides: Axiom before and I enjoyed that, which led me to install this game. I was expecting a similar navigation, unfortunately this installment was a mess compared to Axiom that I didn't bother working through the puzzles. Unlike Axiom, this version was a UX mess: there's no indicator that you've cleared a level, and when levels are connected, it's so hard to remember which level to go back to without selecting them one by one.
Love this game so much!

This is the only game i have felt was worth buying. It is much more than "just binary" as another review has said. That person probably couldn't figure it out. The description says it isnt easy and they didnt lie but it is tantalizingly addictive! (That's a good thing).
Horrible game! No instructions. No goals. Nothing. Just useless binary conversion. DELETED!
Other than some touchscreen hiccups, simply...perfection Everything makes you want to know more, understand better, try harder and, most importantly, keep going.

Das Spiel ist einfach fantastisch! Sehr viele Rätsel die sehr Spaß machen und es wir überhaupt nicht langweilig. Auf so was habe ich immer gewartet und es lohnt sich wirklich es zu holen. Sehr original und eine bestimmt gute Arbeit von den Machern!
Love it! Racks my brain from time to time, but keeps me wanting to figure it out!

Sheer brilliance! If you like puzzles with a challenge and a deep sense of mystery, don't hesitate to pick up everything with "The Guides..." in its title. This game just oozes love for puzzles. Minimalistic, yet richly complex. Broad range of code types with just enough repetition to establish a learning curve. Requires lateral thinking and analytical skills. Pulls you in and never lets you go. Hats off, team!
Exquisite a challenge that I've been seeking for a while now. Thank you for developing this app keep more coming please it's not everyday I come across something worth to put my mind to these days.

I played the free Guides Axiom first. So fun. So hard. I bought this because the developers deserved $ for their excellent work. No rush. Just Figure It Out. I use a notepad. They wanted a review and I am only half done! 5 stars. Math, science, cyphers, puzzles, where is Waldo? This game is it. Example: Guides, Sec 2 Level 25, subtract 64 to generate HYPERSPACE is Not the answer. LMAO. What an excellent distraction and hard to think past. & the correct answer is right there in front of you.
Awesome puzzle design.

I love puzzle games in theory, but most of the ones I've tried have been too simple to be enjoyable. That's not the case here -- this is a uniquely challenging game. Some puzzles are straightforward, but a lot of them really made me work for it. That said, there's not a lot of wiggle room if you get stuck and many of the clues aren't very helpful. I've had to resort to walkthroughs on a couple levels, which is super frustrating -- a puzzle isn't much fun if you need the answer handed to you.

Puzzles are too easy and one-dimensional. Maybe it gets harder as the game progresses, but the developers asked me to review it this far in, so I can only judge this far. It's very easy. The puzzles are just a rotation of the same 4 codes, with some other equally easy puzzles mixed in. If there's only one clue per puzzle to interpret, and only one way to respond to it, then it's not a puzzle, just a clicking adventure.
Absolutely wonderful. I've been playing for an hour straight. It's well thought out and well made. The devs hit a home run with this one.
The learning curve is strong with this one. Very fun
It just threw me in with no explanation, no clues, nothing. The game makes no damn sense and I've had it for 3 days

Amazingly detailed and thought provoking. Got to think outside the box but not too far or you may confuse yourself. Sometimes the simplest solution works. Great mystery weaved into the puzzles making this my favorite game of this style. Great job!

To this day, The Guides, Axiom, and Compendium are probably some of the best mobile games ever released. The graphics and detail in every aspect of this game is simply jaw dropping. Each stage of the game is filled with beautiful details that only serve as a red herring, putting so much into simply distracting you. Some of the later puzzles make you feel like Einstein when you solve them, and that kind of sensation is something that the puzzle game market is lacking at the moment. Outstanding.

There are many cheap 'Puzzle' apps that are mass-market, quick-buck, with little care for quality. THIS IS NOT ONE OF THOSE APPS. This is the kind of stuff you seek out when you're training your brain for escape rooms, or day long puzzle competitions. The presentation, the context clues, it's all wonderfully atmospheric and well put together. Downsides? Well, the UI could use a little clearer description or guidance for the 'help' tools' use, but that's about it. EXCELLENT job.

The Guides is a masterpiece. It offers a unique gaming experience. Sadly

quality developed games like The Guides. Yes, it is a puzzle game... In

teapot and its tau star... the list goes on. Going this deep requires 
purchase of the compendium...

content: This game is great for those looking for a higher level of challenge in puzzle games. I would give it five stars, but I have to admit that it's dauntingly obtuse at some points and could easily turn away players who weren't expecting it to be so difficult. Considering that it has to be purchased, a solution or walkthrough should be offered so that less experienced puzzlers don't feel ripped off. I'd recommend this only to avid puzzle lovers who have the time to go and learn unexpected things, not newbies.

The Guides gives you a cryptic puzzle and an input box for your answer. No direction, no stated goal other then the implied "solve the puzzle," and no clear means to progress. Brilliant, carefully crafted, and very worth your time.
